{
  "texts": [
    "However, we expect this behavior to be absent in real-world scenarios.",
    "(b) Our bandwidth estimation technique relies on the acknowledgment-based mechanism that introduces extra host delays (1-3 ms) on the server side.",
    "As the actual bandwidth increases, the impact of these host delays on network time estimation becomes more significant, resulting in a wider gap between estimated and actual bandwidth values.",
    "Note that for real-world network traces, the estimated bandwidth values may not match precisely the actual bandwidth values since we use the harmonic mean of frequently changing past bandwidth values.",
    "When the error gap is large, Jellyfish adopts a conservative approach."
  ]
}